article.headline: Portland State 84, Northern Arizona 81
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Seamus Boxley scored a career-high 32 points and pulled down 13 rebounds to give Portland State a 84-81 victory over Northern Arizona on Thursday night. The Vikings (15-6, 7-2 Big Sky) remained one-half game ahead of Montana State for first place in the conference standings. Northern Arizona (9-12, 2-6) lost its fourth straight game and had a five-game home-court win streak end. Portland State led 41-32 at halftime and was ahead by as many as 14 points in the second half before the Lumberjacks closed to 72-69 with 2:31 left on Kyle Feuerbach's two free throws. Blake Walker was fouled while hitting a layup and hit the free throw to push Portland State's lead back to 72-69 and Northern Arizona did not threaten again. Boxley had 22 points and seven rebounds in the first half alone and hit 12 of 16 field goals. Vikings guard Will Funn, second in Division I in assists per game, added six points and 12 assists. Blake Walker scored all 17 of his points in the second half for Portland State. Feuerbach led the Lumberjacks with 18 points while Steven Sir added 17 and Ruben Boykin Jr. had 15 points and 10 rebounds.
